input_str: Lonnie George Johnson (born October 6, 1949) is an American inventor and engineer who holds more than 120 patents.[2] He is the inventor of the Super Soaker water gun, which has been among the world's bestselling toys every year since its release.[3]Johnson's father was a World War II veteran and his mother worked as a nurse's aide and they lived in Mobile, Alabama.
